   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>LESSON ELEVEN THE CHURCH-BUILDING SERVICE Scripture Reading: Eph 4:16, 7, 12; 1 Pet 4:10; Rom 12:7a; 16:1; Acts 6:3; 1 Cor 12:28b; Matt 20:26-28; Col 1:7; 4:12, 7; Eph 6:21 OUTLINE The church being built by itself, not only through the joints of supply but also through each one part Eph 4:16.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>To each one of us grace having been given according to the measure of the gift of Christ for the building up of the Body of Christ Eph 4:7, 12.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>As every man has received a gift, even so minister the same to one another, as good stewards of the varied grace of God 1 Pet 4:10.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>The practical service ministry Rom 12:7a; 1 Pet 4:10: As deacons and deaconesses 1 Tim 3:8-13; Phil 1:1; Rom 16:1.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Serving others Acts 6:3.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Helping others 1 Cor 12:28b.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>As a servant, even a slave Matt 20:26-27.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>The examples of such service: The Lord Jesus Matt 20:28.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Epaphras Col 1:7; 4:12.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Tychicus Col 4:7; Eph 6:21.</S>
   </TEXT>
